parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torsion bar can cause the front end of the vehicle to drop, making it difficult to control, and potentially leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The front end of the vehicle drops
the vehicle makes a loud noise
the tire rubs against the wheel well
the vehicle becomes difficult to control
the steering capability of the vehicle is compromised.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Windshield Wiper Motor Circuit Board Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper motor circuit board can cause the windshield wipers to malfunction or stop working, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially during rainy or snowy conditions.
symptoms: windshield wipers do not turn on
windshield wipers work on high speed only
windshield wipers become inoperable during rainy weather conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power window motor can cause the windows to malfunction or become stuck, leading to inconvenience, safety risks, and potential accidents.
symptoms: window does not roll up or down
window motor makes a loud noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Pin Holes in Steel Brake Lines Causing Complete Brake Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The presence of pin holes in steel brake lines can cause complete brake failure, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor
brake pedal feels soft or spongy

Defective rotors can cause brake failure, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
